# Vitest tests (`*.vitest.test.ts`)

## Running and reports

- Fast unit pass (no coverage): **`yarn test:unit`** runs the [Vitest multi-project root](vitest.config.mts) ([testing-terminal-isolation.mdc](testing-terminal-isolation.mdc)): **`unit-electron`**, **`unit-src-renderer`**, **`unit-helpers`**, **`unit-components`**. The root config sets **`root`** to the repository and each project **`extends`** a file under **`vitest/`** so test globs resolve from the repo root (not the config folder).
- Terminal reporting for coverage projects: shared list **`vitestTerminalReporters`** in [vitest.reporters.shared.ts](vitest.reporters.shared.ts) — **`agent`** first (omits noisy per-pass lines; failures and summary still print), then **`json`** to **`test-results/vitest-report/test-results-vitest-*.json`** (paths per **`outputFile`** in each **`vitest/*.config.mts`**).
- Quality gate / coverage: **`yarn testbatch:verify`** ends with **`yarn test:coverage:verify`**, which runs v8 coverage in order: **`yarn test:coverage:electron`** (100% on statements, branches, functions, lines for **`src-electron`**, [vitest.electron.config.mts](vitest/vitest.electron.config.mts)), **`yarn test:coverage:helpers`** (100% on all four for **`helpers/**/*.ts`**, [vitest.helpers.config.mts](vitest/vitest.helpers.config.mts)), **`yarn test:coverage:src`** = [vitest.src-renderer.config.mts](vitest/vitest.src-renderer.config.mts) (**100%** on all four for scoped **`src/`** boot, scripts, stores, **`specialCharactersFixer`**) then [vitest.components.config.mts](vitest/vitest.components.config.mts) (**100%** statements, functions, and lines for **`.ts`** under **`src/components`**, **`src/layouts`**, and **`src/pages`** in the coverage include list; **no** failing branch threshold on that **`.ts`** slice because **v8** can over-count iterator edges; **`.vue`** files have **no** thresholds—**watermarks** use a **60%** lower band so weak Vue totals show red/orange in text/HTML output and should be investigated). The **Vitest coverage tiers (CI)** section below states the same rules as a numbered list. Same chain as **`yarn test:unit:coverage`**.
- Debugging a single project: pass **`--config vitest/vitest.<slice>.config.mts`** (or run **`yarn test:coverage:electron`**, **`yarn test:coverage:helpers`**, **`yarn test:coverage:src`**). A bare **`vitest run --coverage`** without **`--config`** uses the workspace and mixes projects; prefer the explicit scripts above for coverage gates.
- JSON reports: **`test-results/vitest-report/test-results-vitest-electron.json`**, **`...-src-renderer.json`**, **`...-helpers.json`**, **`...-components.json`** (each config’s **`outputFile`**).

## Vitest coverage tiers (CI)

Canonical summary; numbers and **`include`** lists are enforced in **`vitest/*.config.mts`**. Human-oriented copy also lives in **`README.md`** (Quality gate) and **`AGENTS.md`** (Testing expectations).

1. **`src-electron`** — **100%** statements, branches, functions, lines ([vitest.electron.config.mts](vitest/vitest.electron.config.mts)).
2. **`helpers/**/*.ts`** (real helper packages such as **`helpers/playwrightHelpers/`**) — **100%** on all four ([vitest.helpers.config.mts](vitest/vitest.helpers.config.mts)). Workspace tooling under **`vitest/`** is intentionally **not** under **`helpers/`** so this gate stays limited to harness implementation code.
3. **`src`** renderer **`.ts`** in **`unit-src-renderer`** (boot, scripts, stores, **`src/i18n/specialCharactersFixer.ts`**) — **100%** on all four ([vitest.src-renderer.config.mts](vitest/vitest.src-renderer.config.mts)).
4. **`src/components`**, **`src/layouts`**, **`src/pages`** **`.ts`** collected by **`unit-components`** — **100%** statements, functions, and lines; branch totals are printed but **do not** fail CI (**v8** can over-count iterator or loop edges) ([vitest.components.config.mts](vitest/vitest.components.config.mts)).
5. **`.vue`** SFCs in **`unit-components`** — **no** threshold; **`coverage.watermarks`** use a **~60%** lower band. Treat line or statement totals **below 60%** as a review signal to add or extend tests when worthwhile.

**Workspace layout:** [vitest.config.mts](vitest.config.mts) at the repo root sets **`root`** to the repository; each Vitest project **`extends`** one file under **`vitest/`** so globs such as **`src-electron/**`** resolve from the repo root.

## Placement and discovery

- Files must match `**/*vitest.@(spec|test).?(c|m)[jt]s?(x)` — this repo uses **`*.vitest.test.ts`**.
- Co-locate tests under a **`tests/`** directory next to the code under test, e.g. [src/scripts/_utilities/tests](src/scripts/_utilities/tests), [src/stores/tests](src/stores/tests), [src-electron/contentBridgeAPIs/tests](src-electron/contentBridgeAPIs/tests), [src-electron/mainScripts/tests](src-electron/mainScripts/tests) (or **`src-electron/mainScripts/<area>/tests/`** for **`appIdentity/`**, **`windowManagement/`**, **`chromiumFixes/`**, **`userSettings/`**, **`nativeShell/`**, **`ipcManagement/`**), [helpers/playwrightHelpers/tests](helpers/playwrightHelpers/tests) and future **`helpers/<package>/tests/`** trees (Vitest project **`unit-helpers`**), [src/components/elements/FantasiaMascotImage/tests](src/components/elements/FantasiaMascotImage/tests), [src/layouts/tests](src/layouts/tests), [src/pages/tests](src/pages/tests), [src/components/dialogs/DialogProgramSettings/scripts/tests](src/components/dialogs/DialogProgramSettings/scripts/tests) (logic extracted next to an SFC).
- When you add a new package under **`helpers/`** (sibling of **`helpers/playwrightHelpers/`**) or new **`.ts`** modules inside an existing helper package, add or extend **`*.vitest.test.ts`** under that package’s **`tests/`** tree in the **same change** whenever the code contains non-trivial branching, I/O, or public API surface (same expectation as **`src-electron`** and **`src/scripts`** helpers).
- Treat `src/`, `src-electron/`, and **Vue SFCs under `src/components/`**, **`src/layouts/`**, and **`src/pages/`** as Vitest unit-testing surfaces when mounting is appropriate; full UI flows remain in Playwright.
- For **`src/components/**`**, **`src/layouts/**`**, and **`src/pages/**`**, keep a **1:1 baseline**: every feature `.vue` should have a colocated **`tests/<ComponentOrLayoutOrPageName>.vitest.test.ts`** (layouts and pages use the same **`src/<area>/tests/`** folder pattern as existing Storybook previews). When adding, renaming, or removing an SFC, update its matching Vitest file in the same change. **Extracted `scripts/*.ts`** beside a component should carry **focused `scripts/tests/*.vitest.test.ts`** when they introduce testable logic (stores, transforms, toggles)—not every one-line wrapper, but anything you would regret breaking silently.

## Vue and renderer test boundaries

- Use Vitest for deterministic renderer logic in `src/` (helpers, stores/composables, serializable transforms, and simple component-facing logic extracted into TS modules).
- If Vue SFC behavior can be validated without fragile DOM coupling, prefer focused unit tests around the extracted logic path.
- Keep full interaction/visual/integration checks in Playwright component or E2E tests (`*.playwright.test.ts` / `*.playwright.spec.ts`).
- Treat this 1:1 mapping as **coverage presence** for **`.vue`** (no percentage gate); colocated **`.ts`** in the **`unit-components`** coverage **`include`** list must meet the enforced **`.ts`** metrics in [vitest.components.config.mts](vitest/vitest.components.config.mts).
- **`_data/` is for production feeds only** (menus, button lists, locale-backed blobs the app ships). Do **not** put **Vitest fixtures** there.
- **All Vitest fixture data** (sample props, mock objects, expected literals) must live **inside** the same `*.vitest.test.ts` file: inline **`const`** / object literals at module scope next to imports or immediately above the test that uses them. Do **not** add sibling `tests/*.ts` files whose only purpose is to hold data for Vitest. Do **not** use `tests/_data/`.
- **No automated tests for `_data/` modules**: do **not** add Vitest (or Playwright specs) aimed **only** at **any** file under **`_data/`** (e.g. `src/components/**/_data/**`). Cover production `_data` **indirectly** through components or scripts that import it—not with dedicated tests whose SUT is a `_data/` path.
- When selecting mounted DOM in component Vitest files, use the same **`data-test-locator`** / `data-test-*` attribute names as production templates and Playwright (for example `w.get('[data-test-locator="…"]')`); do **not** query bare `data-test`.

## Imports

- From `vitest`: import only what you need — `test`, `expect`, `vi`, `expectTypeOf` (see [tweaks.vitest.test.ts](src-electron/mainScripts/nativeShell/tests/tweaks.vitest.test.ts), [fixAppName.vitest.test.ts](src-electron/mainScripts/appIdentity/tests/fixAppName.vitest.test.ts)).
- **SUT** (system under test): relative import from the parent folder, e.g. `import { appDetailsAPI } from '../appDetailsAPI'`.
- **JSON**: `import packageJSON from '../../../package.json' assert { type: 'json' }` when comparing to package metadata ([fixAppName.vitest.test.ts](src-electron/mainScripts/appIdentity/tests/fixAppName.vitest.test.ts)).
- **Node / app paths**: e.g. `import os from 'os'` only when the test mirrors runtime behavior.

## Documenting each test block

Use a JSDoc comment immediately above `test` or `test.skip` (same style rules as [eslint-typescript.mdc](eslint-typescript.mdc) code comments: no Markdown emphasis in comment text; use single quotes instead of grave accents for inline references). Do not split a single sentence across ` * ` lines for wrapping; use full lines or ` * - ` bullets (see [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) code comments).

1. **First line**: name of the function, API export, or concern (e.g. `determineAppName`, `checkIfExternal`, `startApp`).
2. **Following lines**: scenario, expected behavior, or why the test is skipped — each as a complete line or bullet, not a wrapped continuation of the first line mid-clause.

Examples in the codebase:

- Runnable case: [faExternalLinksManagerAPI.vitest.test.ts](src-electron/contentBridgeAPIs/tests/faExternalLinksManagerAPI.vitest.test.ts) — each `test(...)` is preceded by `checkIfExternal` and a short scenario line.
- Skipped Electron-only: [appManagement.vitest.test.ts](src-electron/mainScripts/tests/appManagement.vitest.test.ts) — `test.skip('...')` with JSDoc explaining that Electron must be running.

## `test` titles

- Use a single **sentence-style string** starting with `Test ...` / `Test if ...` / `Test that ...` / `Test for ...`, matching existing files.

## Runnable tests

- Use `expect(...)`, `expect(...).toBeTypeOf('string')`, `toContain`, etc., as in [appDetailsAPI.vitest.test.ts](src-electron/contentBridgeAPIs/tests/appDetailsAPI.vitest.test.ts) and [extraEnvVariables.vitest.test.ts](src-electron/contentBridgeAPIs/tests/extraEnvVariables.vitest.test.ts).
- Use `vi.stubEnv` for environment-dependent behavior ([fixAppName.vitest.test.ts](../../src-electron/mainScripts/appIdentity/tests/fixAppName.vitest.test.ts)). **Vitest 3+**: for env keys **`DEV`**, **`PROD`**, and **`SSR`**, pass a **boolean** (e.g. `vi.stubEnv('DEV', true)`); other keys use **`string | undefined`**.
- When a test imports **`src-electron`** (or other repo-root) modules and must typecheck under **`tsc`**, prefer the **`app/...`** alias (e.g. `app/src-electron/mainScripts/nativeShell/tweaks`) — see [eslint-typescript.mdc](eslint-typescript.mdc).
- Use `vi.mock(...)` when mocking modules (same files as above).
- Use `expectTypeOf` when asserting type-level consistency ([tweaks.vitest.test.ts](src-electron/mainScripts/nativeShell/tests/tweaks.vitest.test.ts)).
- Avoid `any` in tests and test data; prefer concrete fixture types, generic helpers, or `unknown` with narrowing when values are dynamic.

## Skipped tests (`test.skip`)

- When behavior is explicitly deemed untestable in Vitest, use `test.skip` with the same JSDoc pattern and a clear title.

## File-level notes

- Optional **multi-line block comment** at the top of a file for scope notes (e.g. "Nothing else to test here") — see [extraEnvVariables.vitest.test.ts](src-electron/contentBridgeAPIs/tests/extraEnvVariables.vitest.test.ts).

## Do not

- Do not switch to `describe()` blocks unless the rest of the suite starts using them — **current suites use flat `test` / `test.skip` only**.
- Do not rename `*.vitest.test.ts` — Vitest discovery depends on it.

## Local types extraction rule

- For Vue (`.vue`) and TypeScript (`.ts`) source files, move small file-local interfaces/type aliases into a colocated `<filename>.types.ts` file and import them back.
- For JavaScript (`.js`), TypeScript (`.ts`), Vue (`.vue`), and JSON (`.json`, `.jsonc`, `.json5`) files, enforce expanded multi-line object literals via ESLint (`object-curly-newline` + `object-property-newline`) and keep files auto-fixable with `eslint --fix`.
